cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as automated ICD coding from clinical text. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for this task, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with extracting relevant information from clinical text. Finally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the potential impact of automated ICD coding on healthcare billing and labor.
